&lt;p id="V44MmI"&gt;The suit was filed by several leading Canadian media companies, including the owners of the &lt;em&gt;National Post&lt;/em&gt; and &lt;em&gt;Toronto Star&lt;/em&gt;, &lt;em&gt;The Globe and Mail&lt;/em&gt;, &lt;em&gt;The Canadian Press&lt;/em&gt;, and CBC/Radio-Canada. The group alleges that OpenAI infringed on its copyrights when training its models, like ChatGPT, without seeking permission or offering compensation. &lt;/p&gt;
